item.description:
the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation through NPM registry.
Install: npm install -g codefresh
Install a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: npm install -g codefresh
Update to a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@${VERSION}

Description Create a config context.
Command codefresh create context config &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a config. codefresh create context config my-config -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

Description Delete a helm release from a kubernetes cluster.
Command codefresh delete-release &lt;name&gt;
Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --cluster -c  Run on cluster. required   --timeout -t 300 time in seconds to wait for any individual kubernetes operation (like Jobs for hooks) (default 300)   --purge -p  remove the release from the store and make its name free for later use (default true)   --detach -d  Run pipeline and print build ID   --no-hooks --nh  prevent hooks from running during deletion   --tiller-namespace -n kube-system prevent hooks from running during deletion    Examples Delete release &ldquo;my-release&rdquo; from cluster &ldquo;my-cluster&rdquo; codefresh delete-release my-release --cluster my-cluster

Description Integrate a standard container registry into Codefresh.
Command codefresh create registry standard &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Registry name    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --username   Username to access the docker registry. required   --password   Password to access the docker registry.

the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation using YARN.
Install: yarn global add codefresh
Install a specific version: yarn global add codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: yarn global upgrade codefresh
Update to a specific version: yarn global upgrade codefresh@{VERSION}

Description Create a composition.
Command codefresh create composition &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh create com &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of composition    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource   --compose-file -c  Path to docker-compose.

Description Create a team.
You can create a new team specifying only name of team or specify path to json file for include extended options
Possible fields in file:
name - team name (specifying name in file will rewrite name specified as command argument) users - array of users id for that team tags - array of tag names.
Command codefresh create teams &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh create team &lt;name&gt;

Description Create a secret context.
Command codefresh create context secret &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a secret. codefresh create context secret my-secret -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

Description Show logs of a build.
Command codefresh logs &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Build id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --f   Continue showing build logs until it will finish    Examples Get logs of build ID codefresh logs ID

You can run the CLI using our official docker image which is published to Dockerhub
Pull the latest version: docker pull codefresh/cli
Pull a specific version: docker pull codefresh/cli:${VERSION}

